00:41:03.570 --> 00:41:05.990
Here's what the Toolkit looks like

00:41:05.990 --> 00:41:08.860
and how you can use it to improve care.

00:41:08.860 --> 00:41:12.090
It's primarily designed to
assist healthcare providers,

00:41:12.090 --> 00:41:15.410
patients, and their supporters
who are accessing care.

00:41:15.410 --> 00:41:17.390
It's split into two parts.

00:41:17.390 --> 00:41:20.570
There's a section targeted at
patients and their supporters

00:41:20.570 --> 00:41:23.260
and another part for healthcare providers.

00:41:23.260 --> 00:41:26.400
It consists of information and worksheets

00:41:26.400 --> 00:41:28.890
and the interactive tool that
we've been talking about,

00:41:28.890 --> 00:41:33.000
that helps create the
personalized-accommodation report.

00:41:33.000 --> 00:41:37.560
The color themes and the
font sizes can be changed

00:41:37.560 --> 00:41:40.240
to meet user needs and preferences,

00:41:40.240 --> 00:41:43.120
as well as an array of
accessibility features.

00:41:43.120 --> 00:41:45.081
It has read-aloud options.

00:41:45.081 --> 00:41:48.050
It's accessible to screen readers.

00:41:48.050 --> 00:41:51.730
It has ways to collapse
and simplify information

00:41:51.730 --> 00:41:54.250
for less clutter and distraction.

00:41:54.250 --> 00:41:57.380
In other words, all
that work that we put in

00:41:57.380 --> 00:42:00.730
to learning how to work
effectively with autistic people,

00:42:00.730 --> 00:42:03.890
was built right into the
structure of the tool,

00:42:03.890 --> 00:42:06.588
and makes it a very
different kind of website

00:42:06.588 --> 00:42:11.573
than others that are on the market.

00:42:14.830 --> 00:42:16.830
The section on Healthcare Providers

00:42:16.830 --> 00:42:19.830
includes basic information on autism.

00:42:19.830 --> 00:42:21.824
It has tips for providing care,

00:42:21.824 --> 00:42:25.360
discussions of legal and
ethical considerations,

00:42:25.360 --> 00:42:28.530
such as how to obtain
informed consent, and

00:42:28.530 --> 00:42:32.180
information on medical conditions
and resources and links.

00:42:32.180 --> 00:42:36.730
And, again, this is all generated from

00:42:36.730 --> 00:42:41.730
this very robust process,
collaborative process,

00:42:42.290 --> 00:42:45.320
so very much informed by
people's learned experiences

00:42:45.320 --> 00:42:48.543
as well as the academic input.

00:42:50.920 --> 00:42:53.300
The Patients &amp; Supporters section

00:42:53.300 --> 00:42:57.740
has information on healthcare,
staying healthy, rights,

00:42:57.740 --> 00:42:59.500
and it has checklists and worksheets

00:42:59.500 --> 00:43:02.570
to help people access and
manage their healthcare.

00:43:02.570 --> 00:43:04.700
For example, there are tools to help

00:43:04.700 --> 00:43:08.090
walk people through the process
of making an appointment,

00:43:08.090 --> 00:43:10.330
what to bring to an appointment,

00:43:10.330 --> 00:43:13.183
and worksheets to help people
describe their symptoms.

00:43:14.640 --> 00:43:17.640
Of course, it has the
personalized-accommodations report

00:43:17.640 --> 00:43:19.173
you can see at the top there.

00:43:25.080 --> 00:43:26.650
When you go into that

00:43:26.650 --> 00:43:30.570
personalized-accommodation report tool,

00:43:30.570 --> 00:43:35.570
here is an example of the
kinds of questions there are.

00:43:35.730 --> 00:43:37.217
So, this question is,

00:43:37.217 --> 00:43:39.237
"What can help you make good decisions

00:43:39.237 --> 00:43:40.620
"about your healthcare?"

00:43:40.620 --> 00:43:42.837
And you can pick up to, oh, thanks,

00:43:42.837 --> 00:43:46.350
You can pick up to three choices.

00:43:46.350 --> 00:43:49.377
So, possible suggestions
include things like,

00:43:49.377 --> 00:43:51.967
"Give me very blunt and concrete examples

00:43:51.967 --> 00:43:54.227
"of what could happen if I did or did not

00:43:54.227 --> 00:43:56.240
"follow a recommendation."

00:43:56.240 --> 00:43:58.357
Or "Let me discuss my choices first

00:43:58.357 --> 00:44:01.470
"with a person I trust and
then come back to you."

00:44:01.470 --> 00:44:03.890
I think that's a really important point,

00:44:03.890 --> 00:44:06.310
not just from this tool, but in

00:44:06.310 --> 00:44:10.860
applying the processes that we
were talking about with Dora

00:44:11.730 --> 00:44:14.920
and about how

00:44:16.150 --> 00:44:17.730
people may not be able to

00:44:17.730 --> 00:44:20.300
participate in a healthcare appointment

00:44:20.300 --> 00:44:22.160
or in a person-centered planning meeting

00:44:22.160 --> 00:44:26.650
or in a research group or
another group in real-time.

00:44:26.650 --> 00:44:29.041
And so, being able to step back

00:44:29.041 --> 00:44:32.300
and do some of the work in other settings

00:44:32.300 --> 00:44:33.552
can allow people to participate

00:44:33.552 --> 00:44:35.600
rather than just assuming that,

00:44:35.600 --> 00:44:37.530
if they can't participate in real-time,

00:44:37.530 --> 00:44:39.470
that they can't participate at all.

00:44:39.470 --> 00:44:41.563
I think that's really important.

00:44:41.563 --> 00:44:45.860
Often people are worried that

00:44:45.860 --> 00:44:47.228
if they get an accommodation letter,

00:44:47.228 --> 00:44:50.060
it's going to have a lot of
money associated with it,

00:44:50.060 --> 00:44:52.640
it's going to be difficult to implement

00:44:52.640 --> 00:44:54.530
or complicated to implement.

00:44:54.530 --> 00:44:56.630
Sometimes people need
things that cost money

00:44:56.630 --> 00:44:59.150
and sometimes it does take time and effort

00:44:59.150 --> 00:45:00.710
and I don't wanna minimize that,

00:45:00.710 --> 00:45:03.470
but a lot of the most effective things

00:45:03.470 --> 00:45:05.162
are pretty simple and easy.

00:45:05.162 --> 00:45:06.711
The trick is to know what they are

00:45:06.711 --> 00:45:10.080
and you can actually save a lot of time

00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:14.183
and save a lot of money
by getting it right.

00:45:19.010 --> 00:45:22.480
The Office of Developmental
Primary Care at UCSF

00:45:22.480 --> 00:45:23.740
isn't a research group,

00:45:23.740 --> 00:45:26.730
but we apply many of the same principles

00:45:26.730 --> 00:45:29.930
to our clinical and training work.

00:45:29.930 --> 00:45:33.040
And, we also partner with stakeholders,

00:45:33.040 --> 00:45:35.810
a variety of stakeholders,
to create resources

00:45:35.810 --> 00:45:40.070
that are also available
free on our website.

00:45:40.070 --> 00:45:41.190
There it is up there.

00:45:41.190 --> 00:45:42.320
You can visit it. It's free.

00:45:42.320 --> 00:45:43.270
It's there for you.

